==English==
===Etymology===
Persian/Urdu {{FAchar|[[سپاهي]]}} (sipāhī) ‘soldier, horseman’, from {{FAchar|[[سپاه]]}} (sipāh) ‘army’.  Compare [[spahi]].

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'si:pɔɪ/

===Noun===
{{en-noun|sepoy|sepoys}}

#A native of India employed as a soldier in the service of the British army.